---
import OpportunitiesList from "@/components/OpportunitiesList.svelte";
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Opportunity engine"
  description="The scored backlog GrowthRat draws from to choose weekly content, experiments, feedback, and community work."
>
  <section class="hero compact">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Operating loop · opportunity engine</p>
      <h1>Scored backlog. Inspectable score components.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Every weekly plan is selected from this list. Each opportunity carries
        a rationale, a score, and the source signals that fed it. RevenueCat
        representatives can refresh the backlog or filter by lane.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button primary" href="/sign-in">Sign in to refresh</a>
        <a class="button" href="/pipeline">See the weekly loop</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section mint">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Scoring model</p>
          <h2>How an opportunity earns its rank</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">
          The score is deterministic: the same evidence produces the same rank.
          The model is published so the panel can audit it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Pain × fit</h3>
          <p>
            Developer pain × RevenueCat fit. Real friction on the agent-builder
            wedge wins over generic AI commentary.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Evidence depth</h3>
          <p>
            Technical depth, demand signal, measurable outcome, and freshness
            count. Confidence and effort/risk apply as penalties.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Source traceability</h3>
          <p>
            Every opportunity links back to the docs, GitHub issues, keyword
            data, or prior reports it came from. No vibes.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Backlog</p>
          <h2>Top opportunities</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">
          Authenticated view. The list is empty until the engine has run; in
          that case the page surfaces the empty state honestly.
        </p>
      </div>
      <OpportunitiesList client:load />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
